The Dirac measure at a point assigns measure 1 to sets containing that point and 0 otherwise. So `measureOf S = if π ∈ S then 1 else 0`.

For the monotonicity property, if S ⊆ T, then if π ∈ S then π ∈ T, so the measure of S ≤ measure of T.

